releaseNotes:
This release contains the following products:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Job execution:&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;ARC &lt;/b&gt;v. 13.11.1 released in SL5, and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is a minor release, fixing a number of bugs and introducing several new features like Rucio or Axix. Some components were deprecated ( arc-ur-logger, GACL-related and DQ2 DMC) and some are replaced by new commands.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;File Access, File Transfer, Storage Management:
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;DPM&lt;/b&gt; v. 1.8.8 released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This release provides some new features which were required for the recompilation of many plugins together with a new DB connection pooling indmlite-adapter and mysql which prevents a deadlock under load of dpm-xrootd andwebdav. Also several bug fixes and improvements are adressed namely those related with the mountpoints /dpm.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Job Scheduling:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;GridWay&lt;/b&gt; v. 5.14.2 released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is a repackaged release due to some missing dependencies&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;WMS&lt;/b&gt; v. 3.6.4 released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is a bug fix release which solves the problem of the&amp;nbsp; job submission fails when job ID starts with a dash and WMS callout to LCMAPS.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Client Tools:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;CREAM-UI&lt;/b&gt; v.1.15.3 released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This release fixes some minor issues namelly one with the glite-ce-job-output and glite-ce-job-status.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;dCache-srmclient&lt;/b&gt; v. 2.2.22 released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;This release provides support for SHA2 certificates and it now uses by default jblovus 2.0. Migrating to this version of SRM Client is therefore recommended. This release also solves the jumbo proxy issue.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Metadata Catalogue:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;LFC&lt;/b&gt; v. 1.8.8&amp;nbsp; released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;No new features or improvements; released from the same source code as DPM 1.8.8&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Other:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;BDII core&lt;/b&gt; v. 1.5.7&amp;nbsp; released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This release provides a new version of the glue-validator together with the glite-info-provider-service which contains some fixes for minor bugs. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;GSI-SSHTerm&lt;/b&gt; v. 2.1.0 released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is a minor release and now GSISSH uses JGlobus 2.0.6 in order to patch Windows error. Also a fix is providede in order to solve the expired proxy bug due to change in return error message.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;GridSite&lt;/b&gt; v. 2.2.3 released in both Sl5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is a revision of GridSite, fixing improperly initiated time constants in signature verification code.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;CANl&lt;/b&gt; v. 2.2.2 released in SL5, SL6&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;This release fixes some of the problems found in certificate chain validation.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;There are also new versions of:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;
    &lt;b&gt;bouncycastle-mail&lt;/b&gt;, 1.46-2 solving &lt;a class=&quot;moz-txt-link-freetext&quot; href=&quot;https://ggus.eu/index.php?mode=ticket_info&amp;amp;ticket_id=104768&quot;&gt;https://ggus.eu/index.php?mode=ticket_info&amp;amp;ticket_id=104768&lt;/a&gt;
    - &quot; Job submission fails for VOs supported by VOMS server with
    SHA-512 host certificate&quot;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;
    &lt;b&gt;umd-release&lt;/b&gt;, 3.0.1, containing more signatures, EPEL's and QCG's&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
